photo.alt: Tumblr screenshot. @bellezalatina: There’s a dish called “Rosca de Reyes”, it’s a cake with slices of fruit. Inside of it, they place a small baby shaped figure that represents baby Jesus. This year, in Mexico, people were selling the cake with figures of Baby Yoda instead of the baby Jesus. So, conservative groups are extremely upset about it, and are calling it a direct attack to family values and religion. So now, Baby Yoda is considered a LGBT icon for making furious those conservative, homophobic people.

A screenshot of an article title in spanish that translates into: Brady Yoda Rosa is a direct attack to religion: national front for the family, followed by an image of baby yoda in front of a gay flag. Tumblr user @theunstablejester adds: the LG on LGBT stands for Latine Grogu
